            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>Dukes, a quarterback who transferred from Nebraska, passed for 73 yards, including a 35-yard touchdown to Jomar Wright. He also threw an interception.</p>
<p>&ldquo;[Dukes] made some mistakes, but the thing I was most proud of is that he kept going,&rdquo; Roof said. &ldquo;He took it by the reins and ran with it. I was pleased to see that.&rdquo;</p>
<p>With the addition of Dukes to the quarterback carousel, the players performance on the practice field will decide next week&rsquo;s starter, but Roof said it is &ldquo;incredibly possible&rdquo; that Dukes may see some action as quarterback against the Terrapins. Roof said he hopes, however, that eventually one quarterback will separate himself from the trio.</p>
<p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;d really like to be a one quarterback team,&rdquo; Roof said. &ldquo;Right now its just not something we&rsquo;re ready to do.&rdquo;</p>
<p>Filling the void at the skill positions, a number of young and inexperienced players have gained valuable playing time.</p>
<p>&ldquo;You try and look for the silver lining in every cloud,&rdquo; Roof said. &ldquo;From an injury perspective, the way I look at it right now is that some of these young guys are getting reps right now that&rsquo;ll give us some quality depth when we get everyone back.&rdquo;</p>
<p>Although the team&rsquo;s play has yet to translate into wins, Roof has been impressed with the development from week to week.</p>
<p>&ldquo;I think we&rsquo;re improving,&rdquo; Roof said. &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve seen big strides. I think we&rsquo;ve had a lot of kids that have gotten some real experience in some close ball games, but we&rsquo;re not where we wanted to be.&rdquo;</p>

                                                    <div class="related my-4 py-4 d-print-none">
